  "time_ut": 1646841567,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc2\u0dcf \u0db4\u0dd0\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The triposha packet for pregnant women has also been removed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Women's Day has to be celebrated in a regime that has broken the backs of women and destroyed them, said Mrs. Talatha Athukorala, Member of Parliament in Colombo.",
        "The MP also mentioned that the government that came to ensure the security of the country has deprived the pregnant mother of everything since her triposha.",
        "Mrs. Thalatha Athukorala said the following while attending a press conference held at the opposition leader's office in Marx Fernando Mawatha, Colombo.",
        "\"During the celebration of Women's Day, women in this country have lost their right to live and freedom of speech. All the rights given to live democratically through the constitution have been lost. Today, we as women have to rally against the dictatorial regime led by the President and this government.",
        "Whether talking about the economy or calling the house Buddha mother, the strength of the woman has been broken and destroyed today. This government, which came to ensure the security of the country, has destroyed everything from the triphosha of the pregnant mother who is about to give birth to a child. From women to pregnant women, everything has been destroyed.",
        "As women, we are deeply saddened by the disgraceful insult done by the mighty bully power to our former member of Parliament Mrs. Hirunika Premachandra the other day.",
        "There has never been an era when a woman was subjected to such oppression. A child never lost milk powder. Pregnant mothers were not deprived of triphosha. And at least there were no queues for gas and oil before.",
        "There is no power to express an opinion under the president who came to make law to make security. The same situation has arisen in the parliament today. There is no control of the chamber. Such thugs are given positions and through them we are working to suppress the voices raised democratically."
      ],
